<H3> <TI>   Ukraine Transfers Nuclear Warheads to Russia Amid Fuel Controversy </TI></H3>
<H4>   Russian Official Says Moscow Will Remove Warheads </H4>
<F P=102> LD0203201494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1920 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0203201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A high-ranking Russian military official told 
Interfax on Wednesday that Russia was to begin the withdrawal of 
strategic missiles from Ukraine at the beginning of March. He 
also said that the first lot consisted of 60 warheads removed 
from the strategic missiles of the 46th missile division and 
43rd missile army. There are about 2,000 nuclear warheads in 
Ukraine. 
  He expressed satisfaction that Moscow and Kiev had found a 
political solution of this problem. He also said that delays in 
the withdrawal of the strategic nuclear weapons were due to the 
unpreparedness of corresponding documents. He believes that 
after the necessary papers are prepared by the Ukrainian customs 
and other agencies, there would be no further delays. 

</TEXT>

