<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents] </F>
  [Text] Washington March 5 TASS -- Ukrainian President 
Leonid Kravchuk announced late on Friday that the first train 
with nuclear charges "is on its way from Ukraine to Russia" 
where they are to be dismantled. 
  "Ukraine will fulfil its commitments", Kravchuk told a press 
conference in the White House referring to the agreement 
according to which Ukraine gives up its nuclear weapons. 
  "I am also sure that other countries will fulfill their 
obligations", he added, evidently referring to the nuclear 
security guarantees and financial assistance promised to Ukraine 
by Russia and the United States. 

