<H3> <TI>   No Secret Accord Between Kazakhstan, Ukraine on Baykonur </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703185694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1721 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0703185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A member of the Russian parliament has denied recent 
reports in some of Moscow's newspapers that Kazakhstan and 
Ukraine have a secret agreement on the joint use of the Baykonur 
space- vehicle launching complex. 
  Konstantin Zatulin told a news conference in Almaty, where 
he 
had been monitoring the parliamentary elections as an 
international observer, that Russia and Kazakhstan were going to 
enter into a treaty on the further use of Baykonur. The 
document was due to be signed by the two countries' presidents 
in Moscow on March 30, he said. 
  Commenting on a meeting he had with Kazakh Deputy Prime 
Minister Yerik Asanbayev, Zatulin said Kazakhstan's leadership 
preferred not to bring up the dual citizenship issue, but that 
the next parliament might consider giving Russian the status of 
an official language. 

</TEXT>

