<HEADER>
<AU>   JPRS-TAC-94-002-L </AU>
Document Type:JPRS 
Document Title:Arms Control 

<DATE1>  2 March 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> UKRAINE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement With Japan on Nuclear Weapons Elimination </TI></H3>
<H4>   Zlenko on Agreement </H4>
<F P=102> LD0203164694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1411 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0203164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no dateline as received] -- A framework 
agreement between the Governments of Ukraine and Japan "On 
cooperation in eliminating nuclear weapons in Ukraine and 
setting up a cooperation committee" was signed at Ukraine's 
Foreign Affairs Ministry on 2 March. On behalf of the Ukrainian 
side the agreement was signed by Ukrainian Foreign Minister 
Anatoliy Zlenko and on behalf of the Japanese side by Japan's 
ambassador to Ukraine Shoji Suezawa. "This is the first 
agreement between Japan and the independent Ukraine since the 
establishment of diplomatic relations between our two states in 
1992. Japan hopes Ukraine will confidently travel the road of 
rejecting nuclear weapons and will accede to the Nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty as a non nuclear state," Suedzawa 
stated. Zlenko pointed out that Japan was one of the first 
countries to have signed such an agreement. In his view, "this 
document will promote stronger cooperation between our 
countries. The signing of this agreement is a certain 
contribution to implementing the trilateral statement by the 
Ukrainian, U.S. and Russian presidents, signed on 14 January." 
  A UNIAN correspondent has been informed by the Japanese 
Embassy in Ukraine that the final sum of Japanese aid to 
eliminate nuclear weapons in Ukraine has not been determined yet. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

