<H3> <TI>   Plyushch, German Ambassador Discus Nuclear Disarmament </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303182294 Kiev UT-1 Television Network in Ukrainian 1700 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0303182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UT-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [No video available] </F>
  [Text] Ivan Plyushch, chairman of Ukraine's Supreme 
Council, today received Dr. Alexander Arnot, ambassador 
extraordinary and plenipotentiary of the Federal Republic of 
Germany to Ukraine, at the latter's request. 
  A frank and constructive conversation took place, the main 
subjects of which were Ukraine's further steps along the path of 
nuclear disarmament and the upcoming elections. Ivan 
Stepanovych Plyushch also today met Luis Mareno, ambassador of 
the Commission of the European Communities to Ukraine. The two 
discussed ways of strengthening relations between our state and 
the European Union. 

</TEXT>

