<F P=101> BOLIVIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Quiroga Minimizes Drug Traffickers' Allegations Against Former President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2302212094 La Paz PRESENCIA in Spanish 12 Feb 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PY2302212094 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz PRESENCIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Minister of Government German Quiroga expressed his 
doubts about depositions made by two notorious drug traffickers 
involving former Bolivian President Jaime Paz Zamora in alleged 
meetings with "Thatched Roof" [drug lord Jorge Roca Suarez]. 
Quiroga said: "These depositions have been made by convicts 
linked to drug trafficking." 
  Quiroga said: "It is important not to hurt the dignity of 
citizens, especially those citizens who have occupied our 
nation's highest posts." He noted: "We must not forget the 
status of the people who made these depositions." 
  Quiroga recalled that the depositions were made by criminals 
who had been convicted by the courts of justice for being linked 
to drug trafficking rings. 
  Quiroga nevertheless reported that the depositions, videos, 
and photographs linked to drug trafficking crimes are part of 
the case portfolio sent to the courts of justice yesterday. 
  Minister Quiroga described the evidence as open to the 
public. He said: "It is therefore open to review by national 
public opinion." 
  Quiroga noted: "It is not fair to comment on issues that may 
have been brought up without carrying out an assessment, a 
review, and a complete investigation into these depositions." 
  In response to questions posed by journalists accredited to 
Government Palace, Quiroga pointed out: "There are serious 
contradictions between the depositions of the two drug 
traffickers." He noted: "The courts will make the actual 
assessment and conduct the appropriate investigations." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

