<H3> <TI>   De Greiff Comments on Possible Surrender of Cali Cartel Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2402044494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2402044494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In view of the arrest or possible surrender of Cali 
Cartel members, Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff has 
insisted in his well-known policy of the carrot and the stick. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentifed reporter] Were you aware that 
Gilberto Rodriguez Orejuela and Hector Fabio Urdinola would 
surrender first? 
  [De Greiff] Yes, these are the two people who have appointed 
lawyers with whom we are advancing the process. You can be sure 
that I am confident, and the lawyers have said as much, that the 
process will not be limited to these two people but involve many 
others who unfortunately have engaged in drug trafficking. 
  [Reporter] Will they be the first ones? 
  [De Greiff] That is correct. 
  [Second unidentified reporter] Are we going to be having 
announcements as happened in the past with Pablo Escobar? 
  [De Greiff] Pardon me? 
  [Second reporter] Will we be having announcements of 
surrenders, as happened with Pablo Escobar in the past? 
  [De Greiff] I hope not, because they know and must keep in 
mind that as long as they do not surrender, we are going to 
continue pursuing them. Ultimately, they will meet with either 
Escobar's fate or the fate of those who have surrendered to 
justice. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

