<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   1.5 Tonnes of Cocaine Seized in Quintana Roo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2302150094 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2302150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hector Aguilar; from the "Good Morning From </F>
Mexico" newscast] 
  [Text] Representatives of the Attorney General's Office in 
north Quintana Roo have reported that in a joint operation with 
the Mexican Navy the authorities seized almost 1.5 tons of pure 
Colombian cocaine base packed in 61 packages contained in 24 
bundles. 
  This seizure, which can be described as the most important 
so 
far this year, took place approximately 80 km from Cancun, on 
the beaches of Acumal, where the bundles were dropped into the 
sea from an aircraft. Apparently, the bundles were to be 
illegally transshipped in a 30-meter-long fiberglass boat that 
had a radio with a marine band and other frequencies. 
  The boat and the cocaine are under Navy guard in Cozumel. 
The Federal Judicial Police are investigating the origin of the 
cocaine. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

