<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> VIETNAM </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Seize 230 Kg of Opium, Arrest Suspects in Son La Province </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2202143694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2202143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This week's TIEN PHONG (VANGUARD) Magazine carries 
Quang Binh's article about a case of drug trafficking involving 
more than 230 kg of opium, the biggest drug trafficking case 
discovered so far. The case was discovered by officers of the 
Intersectional Force at the No. 45 Check Point of the Sixth 
National Highways in Son La Province on 25 January. 
  The opium was carried in six gunny sacks and transported in 
a 
car belonging to the Dien Bien Education Department of Lai Chau 
Province with registration number 27A-2278. The car was driven 
by Mr. Nguyen Minh Chau to take Mr. Nguyen Xuan Ngan, acting 
director of the Lai Chau Department of Education and Training, 
and other education cadres to Hanoi for a meeting. 
  According to initial statements made by the suspects, the 
owner of the drug is Mr. Nguyen Dang Quang, age 36 of Gia Luong 
District of Ha Bac Province. He was given a ride to Hanoi. 
  The incident was investigated by law enforcement agencies to 
clarify the involvement of each suspect for a correct trial 
under the law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

