<F P=101> SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest 46 Members of Crime Syndicate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2102085094 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2102085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The police have cracked down on what they described 
as their biggest ever exposure of a crime syndicate in this 
country. In a joint operation in Transvaal and Natal last night, 
they arrested at least 46 members of the syndicate known as the 
Boere Mafia. Fraud and theft amounting to more than 250 million 
rands are involved. Over 300 members of the police took part in 
the operation. Teams were sent as far as Groblersdal to arrest 
members of the Boere Mafia at their homes. All their homes were 
searched thoroughly for evidence. Seventeen stolen vehicles 
were also taken possession of. 
  The suspects will appear in court in Pretoria and 
Pietermaritzburg today on charges of complicity to murder police 
officials, armed robbery, housebreaking, credit card and check 
fraud, and theft. The police have been on the syndicate's trail 
for at least two years. 
  In August last year 19 people were arrested. Some of those 
released on bail at the time were again arrested last night. 
The police say the court cases could take up to three years. 

</TEXT>

