<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses Regulations for Council for Control of Drug Abuse </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202075994 Sofia BTA in English 1945 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202075994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sofia, February 21 (BTA) -- Today the government 
discussed regulations concerning the National Council for 
Control of Drug Abuse and Arms Trafficking. It was established 
by a government decree last August and is chaired by the 
minister of health. It is to develop the legal framework of 
drug control and will be in charge of the prevention of drug 
abuse and the treatment and rehabilitation of drug addicts. It 
will coordinate the actions of all state institutions and will 
collect and analyze data on the matter. The council's financing 
will be provided by the Ministry of Health. [passage omitted] 

