<H3> <TI>   Customs Police Make `Biggest Heroin Haul Since 1970' at Hungarian Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2502201894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1700 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2502201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 25/2/1994 -- The biggest heroin 
haul since 1970 was captured at the Boros customs station, Bihor 
County, a frontier crossing between Romania and Hungary. It is 
about 22 kg of Mexican heroin, 84-88 percent refined, found in a 
Citroen with Dutch registration number LT 79 LH, belonging to 
tourist Jovic Goran, born in Yugoslavia,now having double French 
and Yugoslav citizenship, who intended to leave Romania. The 
"commodity," in 500 gram parcels, was hidden in a specially 
arranged place in the car. 

