<H3> <TI>   Ticino Police Corporal Arrested For Cocaine Trafficking </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2302113994 Bern ATSA/SDAA in French 1606 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BR2302113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed GU/GA: "Ticino Police Corporal Arrested in </F>
Kloten--Implicated in International Traffick of 150 Kilograms of 
Cocaine"; as released by Bern ATSA/SDAA database] 
  [Text] Lugano/Agno, 21 Feb (ATS) -- A Ticino police 
corporal, implicated in a vast international cocaine deal, was 
arrested last Friday at Kloten airport. He had been working for 
six years at Agno airport near Lugano. The man admitted his 
crimes, according to the Lugano public ministry and the canton 
police. 
  Living in Barbengo in the southern suburbs of Lugano, the 40 
year-old police corporal had been under surveillance for several 
weeks. The man was arrested on his return from a trip to Mexico. 
  Immediately questioned by Ticino Prosecutor Jacques Ducry, 
the policeman made confessions. He had been involved, since 
February 1991, in international cocaine trafficking in South 
America, Switzerland, and Italy. A casual cocaine user, the 
Ticino corporal had imported and delivered 150 kg of cocaine, 
making 70,000 Swiss francs. 
  The Ticino authorities stated that the police corporal had 
been in contact with the world of drug traffickers in the course 
of his duties at Lugano airport. The canton's police force 
asked the State Council to suspend the man immediately. The 
corporal was imprisoned at the end of his period in custody. 
The Ticino authorities stressed: "The inquiry is being made at 
an international level and therfore we cannot reveal any more 
information." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

