<H3> <TI>   Deputy Says Youth in Racha Region Imperiled by Drug Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2502171294 Yerevan SNARK in English 0605 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2502171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, February 24 (SNARK)--Young people of Racha 
region in the north of Georgia are on the edge of survival--this 
is the opinion of Soso Makhadiany, the deputy of the Georgian 
parliament. The reason is that during last four months Racha, 
the relatively well-being settlement, transmuted into the center 
of drug business and drug addiction. He said to SNARK that the 
drugs are trafficked in Georgia from Georgia. 
  According to Makhadiany the only way to stop this evil is to 
block the border, that passed through Oni city. The police 
doesn't control the situation, and even more, the authorities of 
the region are involved in the drug business. 

</TEXT>

