<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Drug Seizures, Arrests for 3 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0403031994 </F>
<F P=103> PY0403031994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on drug seizures and arrests related to drug trafficking 
monitored through 3 March. 
<H5>  Argentina </H5>
  National Border Police agents have arrested four members of 
a 
gang of drug traffickers and seized 38 kg of very pure cocaine 
during two operations conducted over the past few hours in the 
city of Salta, the capital of Salta Department. (Buenos Aires 
NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 2005 GMT 26 Feb 94) 
  The Drug Prevention Programming Secretariat has reported 
that 
personnel from the Naval Prefecture, Customs, the Federal 
Police, and the Air Force seized 3,123 kg of cocaine, 2,250 kg 
of marijuana, 14 plants of marijuana, and 2,160 microdoses of 
LSD, and arrested 82 people, during the two-month "Sun Without 
Drugs" campaign in the city of Mar del Plata. (Buenos Aires 
NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 2133 GMT 26 Feb 94) 
<H5>  Peru </H5>
  Six Canadian drug traffickers who are serving 10-15 year 
prison terms in Peruvian jails will be extradited to Canada in 
the next few days. They are Diane Deaudoin Bedard, 46; her 
husband Claude Descoteaux, 45; Sylvie Suzane Jones, 34; her 
husband Leopold Ladouceur, 57; Oscar Arturo Nieri Cavero, 44; 
and Olga Julia Quintana. (Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 23 Feb 94 
p A11) 

</TEXT>

