<F P=101> ARGENTINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Eighty Kg of Cocaine Seized Aboard Ship During Joint Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2602154994 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
0116 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2602154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 25 Feb (NA) -- In an operation 
resulting from the discovery on 24 February of 80 kg of cocaine 
on board the ship Eugenio C, personnel from the National Border 
Police and the Coast Guard seized drugs, cars, money, and 
documents, and arrested six people. 
  In the operation, police raided several homes in the federal 
capital and Greater Buenos Aires and early this morning seized a 
large amount of marijuana; four cars--one Fiat Duna, one Fiat 
Uno, a Volkswagen, and a Ford Falcon; $697; 1.089 million lire; 
various documents; two high-precision scales; and 2 kg of 
different pieces of jewelry and gold bars. During the operation, 
six people were arrested. 
  The overall result of the operation, which began on 24 
February, was the seizure of 120 kg of cocaine and the arrest of 
10 people. 
  The most important part of the operation took place on board 
the Eugenio C, which was about to leave for the Brazilian port 
of Santos, where 80 kg of cocaine were found. 

</TEXT>

