<F P=101> BOLIVIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on Clashes With Coca Growers in Chapare </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0103232094 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0103232094 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Drug trafficking has several faces. One of them is 
what has been occurring in Chapare: clashes between Rural Mobile 
Patrol Unit agents and coca growers. Foreign Minister Antonio 
Aranibar has pointed out that Law 1008 is being strictly 
complied with, and that the clashes that have been taking place 
in Chapare are essentially a result of the fact that new coca 
plantations have been found. 
  [Begin Aranibar recording] This conflictive situation in the 
Chapare region is a result of the national government's 
decision, which has been channeled through the appropriate 
Ministry of Government organizations and the National 
Secretariat for Social Defense, to comply with Law 1008 with 
regard to illegal coca growing in the Chapare region. Coca has 
recently been planted in the region, and this violates Law 1008 
and harms the international commitments made by Bolivia. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

