<H3> <TI>   Bolivian Woman Arrested With 4 Kg of Cocaine Glued in Suitcase Lining </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0229C Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 18 Jan 
94 p 3-4 </F>

<F P=103> 94WD0229C </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article: "PF Seizes Bolivian Woman With Suitcase Lined With </F>
4 Kilos of Cocaine"] 
  [Text] At 2300 the day before yesterday, the PF (Federal 
Police) arrested Editha Enelda Lobo de Ruiz, 28, on a charge of 
drug trafficking. Police officers found about four kg of cocaine 
camouflaged as the inner lining of a suitcase that was in her 
possession. 
  According to the PF, the Bolivian woman had used a resin to 
glue the cocaine to the suitcase. She had arrived at Cumbica 
International Airport in Guarulhos (in Greater Sao Paulo) hours 
earlier on a flight from Santa Cruz de la Sierra, Bolivia. The 
suspect was about to board Varig Flight 766 for Zurich, 
Switzerland. 
  Airport police suspected her because of the weight of the 
briefcase [as published] (about 8.5 kg) and because her passport 
showed that she had made another trip from Santa Cruz de la 
Sierra to Europe--the traditional drug trafficking route--within 
the previous 30 days. According to the PF, the case will have to 
be treated chemically to remove the cocaine paste. Editha was 
taken to a Federal Police cell on Piaui Street in Higienopolis 
(downtown Sao Paulo). She is being held without bail. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

